doc -global --directory and files
doc/ -global only directories



/doc --rootLevel--both doc directoris and files
/doc/-- rootLevel --only directoris




doc --directory or file with name doc [at all levels of project]


leading Slash :
	/doc/ -- only at root level. Doesn't ignore sub directories with name doc.It excludes files.
	/doc -- will include both directory and files with name doc at root level.

trailing Slash:

 doc/ -- will include only directories not files.

